Hikuya hi nhlamuselo ya politiki, '''Tiko''' i ntlawa wa va aka tiko lowu hanyaka ehansi ka xiyimiso xa hulumendhe wun'we.<ref name="oxford-state">{{Cite journal}}</ref>  Matiko man'wana ma fumiwa hi mfumo lowu nga e tikweni rin'wana.<ref>For example, the [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vichy_France Vichy France] (1940-1944) officially referred to itself as ''l'État français'' (the French state).</ref> 



Speakers of American English often use the terms ''state'' and ''government'' as synonyms,<ref group="note">The two are especially synonymous when phrased as "the state" and "the government." </ref> with both words referring to an organized political group that exercises authority over a particular territory.<ref>{{citation|title="state" (definition 5) and "government" (definitions 4, 5, and 6)|work=[[Merriam-Webster Dictionary]]|publisher=Merriam-Webster, Incorporated|year=2015|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/}}</ref>

Vanhu votala va wela enhansi ka nawu wa tiko ro karhi, hambi leswi kungana vanhu lava vativonaka vanga ri hansi ka tiko. Eka malembe-xidzana ya vu 21, vanhu hinkwavo va wela eka mfumo wa tiko.

